 Grey High School matriculant and recent South African-Under 19 representative, Matthew Breetzke, has during his high school tenure, set a new record for the most centuries scored for Grey’s 1st XI cricket. Breetzke set the record of scoring 17 centuries for his school’s 1st XI and was as a result, presented with a cricket bat, boasting a plaque engraved with each one of those centuries scored. Breetzke, who matriculated from Grey High in 2016, has astonishingly totalled over 5000 runs for his school. Image: Matthew Breetzke with his awarded bat. 